casters now give a 25% chance by 2029 and 50% by 2033. One article concludes AGI by 2030 is within expert range and should not be dismissed. The Samotsvety superforecasters estimate ~28% chance by 2030. The 2022 Expert Survey gives a median 50% probability of high-level machine intelligence by 2047, 90% by 2075. The authors stress that expert opinion is inconsistent across groups, and while timelines are shortening, no forecast is highly reliable. AGI definition sensitivity is acknowledged: robotics inclusion makes AGI harder; focusing on AI R&D automation makes it nearer.\",\n    \"AI Multiple\": \"AGI is defined as an AI system matching human cognitive abilities across all tasks. Analysis of 9,800 predictions shows a trend toward the late 2020s/early 2030s, especially after ChatGPT. Most surveys indicate a 50% probability between 2040–2061. The 2022 Expert Survey estimates 50% chance of high-level machine intelligence by 2059. AI Frontiers' Adam Khoja and Laura Hiscott estimate a 50% probability by 2028, 80% by 2030, based on their quantitative definition. Once AGI is reached, most experts believe superintelligence would follow within 2–30 years.\"\n  }\n}"
