ibrosis requires sustained architectural remodeling, the assumption that intermittent enzyme peaks will permanently reverse established scar tissue without continuous, potentially toxic re-dosing is biologically implausible; and (iv) standard LNPs are **not inert** in this context—they can provoke lipotoxicity and inflammation that may further damage a liver already described as being “on the brink of collapse.” Betting on this assumption risks not only clinical failure but also iatrogenic acceleration of liver injury."
